\b\fs24 Terms of Use\b0\fs22\par
\par
By installing the Tamandua EDR Agent, you acknowledge and agree to the following:\par
\par
\b 1. Purpose\b0\par
This software is an Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR) agent designed to monitor system activity, detect security threats, and protect your endpoints from malicious activity.\par
\par
\b 2. Data Collection\b0\par
The agent collects telemetry data including but not limited to:\par
\bullet  Process creation and termination events\par
\bullet  File system activity\par
\bullet  Network connections\par
\bullet  Registry modifications (Windows)\par
\bullet  System events and logs\par
\par
This data is transmitted to your configured EDR server for analysis.\par
\par
\b 3. System Access\b0\par
The agent requires elevated privileges (SYSTEM/root) to perform security monitoring. It operates as a Windows service that starts automatically with your system.\par
\par
\b 4. Warranty Disclaimer\b0\par
THIS SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND. THE AUTHORS AND COPYRIGHT HOLDERS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM THE USE OF THIS SOFTWARE.\par
\par
\b 5. Security\b0\par
You are responsible for:\par
\bullet  Securing the agent token and server credentials\par
\bullet  Configuring appropriate TLS/SSL certificates\par
\bullet  Following security best practices for EDR deployment\par
\par
\b 6. Support\b0\par
For support, documentation, and updates, please visit:\par
\par
\f1     https://tamandua.security\par
\f0\par
\par
\b\fs24 Installation Notes\b0\fs22\par
\par
The installer will:\par
\bullet  Install the Tamandua EDR Agent to Program Files\\Tamandua\par
\bullet  Create a Windows service "TamanduaAgent"\par
\bullet  Configure the service to start automatically\par
\bullet  Create firewall rules for agent communication\par
\bullet  Store configuration in C:\\ProgramData\\Tamandua\par
\par
\b Silent Installation:\b0\par
\f1 msiexec /i tamandua-agent.msi /qn SERVER_URL="wss://..." AGENT_TOKEN="..."\par
\f0\par
By clicking "I Accept" you agree to these terms and conditions.\par
